+{"id":"bd-33w","title":"Parity Closure Program: bvr must fully match legacy bv (robot + TUI + integrations)","description":"Background: bvr currently has meaningful progress but still trails the legacy Go beads_viewer in command surface, integration features, and TUI fidelity.\\nGoal: deliver true feature/functionality parity with explicit proof, not aspirational parity.\\nScope: robot CLI contracts, interactive TUI behavior/appearance, workspace/hooks/export ecosystem, performance and reliability under scale.\\nAcceptance: every legacy surface has a mapped bvr equivalent (or explicit intentional exclusion), parity report reaches complete, and conformance/e2e evidence is green.\\nTesting & logging requirement: all child work must include deterministic tests and verbose diagnostics useful for failure triage in CI and local runs.","status":"blocked","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:52.918444947Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T22:26:28.384552358Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["parity","porting","program"]}
+{"id":"bd-33w.1","title":"Spec-First Parity Contract and Gap Ledger","description":"Background: porting-to-rust guidance requires spec extraction first, implementation second.\\nGoal: create a single authoritative contract for what 'full parity' means.\\nDeliverables: command-by-command behavior contract, field-level output contract, and visual/keybinding TUI contract.\\nAcceptance: implementation teams can work without re-reading legacy ad hoc; all downstream epics reference this contract.","status":"blocked","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:55.093818544Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T22:26:28.474800713Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["parity","planning","spec"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-33w.1","depends_on_id":"bd-33w","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:55.093818544Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-33w.1.1","title":"Build authoritative legacy->bvr command/flag parity ledger","description":"Background: the current gap includes many legacy flags absent in bvr.\\nWork: enumerate every legacy CLI/robot flag, classify status (implemented/partial/missing/excluded), and document exact behavior contracts including defaults and error modes.\\nAcceptance: FEATURE_PARITY.md contains a machine-checkable ledger mapping legacy flags to bvr implementation tasks and tests; no unclassified surfaces remain.\\nTesting/logging: add an automated check that fails if a legacy-mapped flag is removed or undocumented.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:56.009218447Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T22:56:37.156889003Z","closed_at":"2026-02-27T22:56:37.156867743Z","close_reason":"FEATURE_PARITY.md now contains a comprehensive machine-checkable ledger mapping all 129 legacy bv flags to bvr implementation status (19 complete, 27 partial, 59 missing, 12 excluded, 2 bvr-only). Automated parity_ledger_documents_all_implemented_bvr_flags test verifies every implemented flag is documented. No unclassified surfaces remain.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cli","robot","spec"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-33w.1.1","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:56.009218447Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-33w.1.2","title":"Define TUI fidelity contract (layout breakpoints, keymaps, visual tokens)","description":"Background: visual parity requires explicit measurable criteria.\\nWork: capture reference behavior for width bands (~100/140/180), per-view component composition, keybinding semantics, modal flows, and textual/visual tokens (headers, lane cards, indicators).\\nAcceptance: contract doc includes objective pass/fail checks and fixture/screenshots references suitable for automated snapshot validation.\\nTesting/logging: define required snapshot IDs and keyflow scripts that later tasks must satisfy.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:56.086734633Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T23:01:57.304769088Z","closed_at":"2026-02-27T23:01:57.304743230Z","close_reason":"FEATURE_PARITY.md now contains comprehensive TUI Fidelity Contract with: layout structure (42/58 split, header/footer), 5 view mode specifications (Main/Board/Graph/Insights/History), complete keybinding matrix (pass/fail checkable per mode with 60+ bindings), visual token catalog (status/type icons, mini-bars, box drawing, section headers), 3 modal flow specifications (help/quit-confirm/search), and remaining fidelity gaps documented.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["spec","tui","ux"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-33w.1.2","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:56.086734633Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-33w.1.3","title":"Freeze phased implementation and dependency gates from spec contract","description":"Background: parity closure needs sequencing discipline to avoid churn.\\nWork: convert contract into execution waves with explicit prerequisites, blocked-by rules, and completion criteria that tie directly to tests.\\nAcceptance: each downstream epic task links to concrete gates; no work item lacks verification strategy.\\nTesting/logging: add governance checklist to CI docs so unfinished gates are visible.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:56.166638253Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T23:12:43.450703583Z","closed_at":"2026-02-27T23:12:43.450685069Z","close_reason":"FEATURE_PARITY.md now contains a 4-wave phased implementation plan with explicit prerequisites, blocked-by rules, and concrete verification criteria (test names) for every gate. Wave 0 (spec contract) complete, Waves 1-4 mapped to 34 beads across 7 epics. Completion criteria defined: Waves 0-3 for functional equivalence, Wave 4 for release readiness.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["governance","planning","spec"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-33w.1.3","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:56.166638253Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-33w.1.3","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:26:54.693568627Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-33w.1.3","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:26:54.777974984Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-33w.2","title":"Robot/CLI Surface Parity (Legacy 134 flags -> Rust complete coverage)","description":"Background: legacy bv exposes many robot and operational flags not yet in bvr.\\nGoal: close robot/CLI functional gap while preserving deterministic machine-readable contracts.\\nScope: missing robot commands, search/recipes/drift/schema/docs output surfaces, update/admin flags, and compatibility semantics.\\nAcceptance: all required legacy flags are either implemented with conformance evidence or explicitly excluded in spec with rationale.","status":"blocked","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:55.175200454Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T22:26:28.567071187Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cli","parity","robot"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-33w.2","depends_on_id":"bd-33w","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:55.175200454Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-33w.2","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:59.388150962Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-33w.2.1","title":"Implement robot contract utilities: --robot-docs, --robot-schema, --schema-command, format stats parity","description":"Background: machine consumers rely on discoverability and schema guarantees.\\nWork: add missing robot docs/schema surfaces, retain json/toon contract compatibility, and parity behavior for output format diagnostics.\\nAcceptance: command outputs are fixture-tested against expected contract fields and error handling behavior.\\nTesting/logging: per-command unit tests + conformance fixture checks + stderr diagnostics snapshots.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:56.242418376Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-28T00:46:13.217470015Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cli","robot","schema"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-33w.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:26:29.217280383Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-33w.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:26:29.306606209Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-33w.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:56.242418376Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-33w.2.2","title":"Port recipe and script workflow surfaces: --robot-recipes, --recipe, --emit-script, feedback controls","description":"Background: operators need recipe-driven prioritization and script emission for agent workflows.\\nWork: implement recipe listing/application, script generation with format/limit controls, and feedback tuning commands (accept/ignore/show/reset).\\nAcceptance: script outputs deterministic, recipe behaviors match documented semantics, feedback visibly influences recommendation weights.\\nTesting/logging: fixture tests for recipe outputs and emitted scripts; explicit logs showing applied weight deltas.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:56.320261275Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:59.894773394Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["automation","recipes","robot"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-33w.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:56.320261275Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-33w.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:59.894732677Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-33w.2.3","title":"Port label intelligence and drift baseline surfaces","description":"Background: label-level health and drift monitoring are core triage capabilities in legacy bv.\\nWork: implement --robot-label-health/flow/attention (+ --attention-limit), save/check baseline commands, and --robot-drift output.\\nAcceptance: outputs include legacy-equivalent aggregates, filtering semantics, and stable ordering.\\nTesting/logging: conformance fixtures for each command with edge cases (empty labels, no baseline, severe drift).","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:56.397373093Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:59.996765475Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["drift","labels","robot"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-33w.2.3","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:56.397373093Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-33w.2.3","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:59.996731982Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-33w.2.4","title":"Port semantic search and ranking controls","description":"Background: search and hybrid reranking surfaces are currently missing.\\nWork: implement --search/--robot-search with search-limit, search-mode, search-preset, and search-weights semantics, including deterministic fallbacks when index state changes.\\nAcceptance: parity tests verify ranking behavior on canonical fixtures and parameter validation/error messages.\\nTesting/logging: include detailed ranking-factor traces in debug logs for reproducibility.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:56.476645851Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T22:26:00.082103037Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ranking","robot","search"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-33w.2.4","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:56.476645851Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-33w.2.4","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:26:00.082040200Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
